title:Fruit Pizza
ingredients:Cooking spray//
2 cups flour//
1/2 cup powdered sugar//
1 cup cold butter//
1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese, softened//
1/3 cup white sugar//
1 teaspoon almond extract//
2 cups sliced strawberries//
1 cup blueberries//
i kiwi, sliced//
1 cup pineapple juice//
1/2 cup white sugar for glaze//
2 tablespoons cornstarch//
1 teaspoon lemon juice
instructions:Preheat oven to 350F.//
Lightly spray 12 inch round pizza pan.//
Combine flour and powdered sugar om a bowl.//
Cut in butter with knife until mixture resemble coarse crumbs.//
Press into pizza pan to make crust.//
Bake for 12-15 minutes, cool on wire rack.//
Beat cream cheese, 1/3 cup white sugar, and almond extract until smooth.//
Spread over cooled crust.//
Arrange strawberries, blueberries, and kiwi over mixture.//
mix pineapple juice, 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch, and lemon juice in a saucepan until smooth.//
Bring to boil, stir until thickened, about 2 minutes.//
Cool and slightly drizzle over fruit.//
Refrigerate until chilled.